WEBVTT

1
00:01:03.814 --> 00:01:05.941
Glad news. Lord Ormund!

2
00:01:07.150 --> 00:01:09.069
The war is ended.
your allies have scattered.

3
00:01:09.152 --> 00:01:10.821
and your nephews fled.

4
00:01:10.904 --> 00:01:13.615
There is a new queen
and she sits her father's throne.

5
00:01:15.450 --> 00:01:17.035
We heard rumor of this.

6
00:01:18.287 --> 00:01:21.039
Though on the road.
rumors swarm like flies.

7
00:01:21.123 --> 00:01:22.708
Well. the queen. in her wisdom.
offered you clemency.

8
00:01:22.791 --> 00:01:24.209
and your army with you.

9
00:01:25.085 --> 00:01:27.337
Only bend the knee
and swear your allegiance.

10
00:01:27.420 --> 00:01:30.173
and you may return to Oldtown
and live your lives in...

11
00:01:31.091 --> 00:01:32.092
peace.

12
00:01:32.175 --> 00:01:34.261
Have you any proof of your claim?

13
00:01:34.344 --> 00:01:38.973
Or am I to trust in the reliability
and rectitude of the Rogue Prince?

14
00:01:39.057 --> 00:01:41.602
Trust me or don't.
You will encounter the truth soon enough.

15
00:01:42.603 --> 00:01:44.854
Your uncle Otto encountered it
very recently...

16
00:01:45.771 --> 00:01:47.691
and the Hightower guard soon after him.

17
00:01:50.402 --> 00:01:52.446
And if I am inclined to fight?

18
00:01:52.529 --> 00:01:54.156
That seems obvious enough.

19
00:01:54.239 --> 00:01:56.575
No need to sully the pleasantness
of this meeting.

20
00:02:00.078 --> 00:02:03.415
Though I must say. I think Ulf there

21
00:02:03.498 --> 00:02:06.501
would very much enjoy settling into
your chambers in the High Tower.

22
00:02:06.585 --> 00:02:09.545
Would you like to be Lord of Oldtown. Ulf?

23
00:02:18.263 --> 00:02:19.806
I am left no choice.

24
00:02:21.224 --> 00:02:23.185
For myself. I would resist.

25
00:02:24.353 --> 00:02:26.688
But I have many other lives to consider.

26
00:02:27.939 --> 00:02:29.983
And so. in the interest of peace...

27
00:02:32.069 --> 00:02:33.070
I will submit.

28
00:02:33.153 --> 00:02:34.321
Delightful.

29
00:02:46.792 --> 00:02:49.127
I. Ormund Hightower.

30
00:02:49.211 --> 00:02:50.712
promise to be faithful

31
00:02:50.796 --> 00:02:53.340
to Rhaenyra Targaryen. the queen.

32
00:02:53.423 --> 00:02:55.550
I pledge my fealty to her.

33
00:02:55.634 --> 00:02:59.304
You have chosen wisely.
if reluctantly. Lord Ormund.

34
00:02:59.388 --> 00:03:02.683
Turn around now and lead your army home.
and you will be spared.

35
00:03:15.153 --> 00:03:16.947
Our campaign has ended.

36
00:03:18.407 --> 00:03:20.325
We take the Roseroad homeward.

37
00:03:21.702 --> 00:03:22.703
Ah!

38
00:03:25.204 --> 00:03:27.249
I almost forgot.

39
00:03:28.917 --> 00:03:30.043
Your ward...

40
00:03:31.211 --> 00:03:33.004
Daeron Targaryen.

41
00:03:33.088 --> 00:03:34.381
He'll be coming with me.

42
00:03:38.301 --> 00:03:39.928
You would take him hostage?

43
00:03:40.011 --> 00:03:41.555
It would be rather an oversight to allow

44
00:03:41.638 --> 00:03:43.724
one of Prince Aegon's heirs
to go prancing about the Reach

45
00:03:43.807 --> 00:03:45.559
with his dragon. no less.

46
00:03:45.642 --> 00:03:49.187
We will treat him kindly.
as we would any son of Viserys.

47
00:03:50.105 --> 00:03:51.773
As long as you behave yourself.

48
00:04:24.723 --> 00:04:26.349
Be brave. young prince.

49
00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:44.409
Well met. nephew.

50
00:04:45.994 --> 00:04:47.037
Go home.

51
00:06:50.243 --> 00:06:52.704
The air is thick with ghosts.

52
00:06:59.002 --> 00:07:00.253
Not unhappy ones.

53
00:07:01.087 --> 00:07:02.589
I see myself as a child coming to...

54
00:07:04.633 --> 00:07:06.217
play him a tune I had learned.

55
00:07:09.429 --> 00:07:10.805
He was strong then.

56
00:07:12.933 --> 00:07:14.100
And my mother.

57
00:07:20.857 --> 00:07:23.026
Lord Ormund surrendered.

58
00:07:24.069 --> 00:07:25.862
We have your little prince.

59
00:07:26.696 --> 00:07:28.949
Though I still say we should
have incinerated them all.

60
00:07:32.118 --> 00:07:34.746
I must justify my father's faith in me.

61
00:07:37.165 --> 00:07:39.459
Rule as he would have wished.

62
00:07:43.421 --> 00:07:45.006
At any rate. we must begin.

63
00:07:52.180 --> 00:07:54.641
The sooner I'm formally crowned.
the better.

64
00:07:55.683 --> 00:07:57.811
Though the preparations
are no small undertaking.

65
00:07:58.853 --> 00:08:01.564
To house and feed all those
who must attend. to...

66
00:08:02.899 --> 00:08:04.401
organize tourneys.

67
00:08:04.484 --> 00:08:05.694
The grand procession.

68
00:08:07.028 --> 00:08:08.029
Ah.

69
00:08:09.781 --> 00:08:12.492
Daeron Targaryen. Your Grace.

70
00:08:17.664 --> 00:08:19.457
We've not met.

71
00:08:19.541 --> 00:08:22.877
I'm your half-sister
and our father's chosen heir.

72
00:08:24.462 --> 00:08:27.340
You've flown in service of your brother.
the usurper.

73
00:08:27.424 --> 00:08:28.591
What have you to say?

74
00:08:31.094 --> 00:08:33.179
Open your mouth and speak to your queen.

75
00:08:33.263 --> 00:08:34.889
You are a prisoner in this house.

76
00:08:36.099 --> 00:08:39.894
Your treatment will depend on
your conduct and your pliancy.

77
00:08:39.977 --> 00:08:40.979
Look at me.

78
00:08:41.813 --> 00:08:46.192
I wish to know what Ormund knew
of the conspiracy to deny me my throne.

79
00:08:48.361 --> 00:08:50.947
What of Aemond. then? Or Aegon?

80
00:08:52.282 --> 00:08:54.284
What do you know of their movements?

81
00:08:57.579 --> 00:08:59.581
Oh. as you wish.

82
00:08:59.664 --> 00:09:00.874
Confine him to a chamber.

83
00:09:02.333 --> 00:09:03.626
Coming down!

84
00:09:08.757 --> 00:09:11.926
He's younger than I imagined.

85
00:09:12.010 --> 00:09:14.220
He's a claimant to the throne.

86
00:09:14.304 --> 00:09:16.014
You're going to have to kill him.

87
00:09:16.097 --> 00:09:17.849
...was Tyland Lannister.

88
00:09:17.932 --> 00:09:19.184
He did not confide in me.

89
00:09:19.267 --> 00:09:21.394
I know only that he spoke
of dividing the gold

90
00:09:21.478 --> 00:09:23.480
and sending it out of the city
for safekeeping.

91
00:09:23.563 --> 00:09:25.231
-What gold?
-It appears. Your Grace.

92
00:09:25.315 --> 00:09:26.775
the crown's wealth has been taken.

93
00:09:26.858 --> 00:09:29.569
-Taken?
-Your treasury is depleted.

94
00:09:29.652 --> 00:09:32.238
There is enough to see
your court through a week or two.

95
00:09:32.322 --> 00:09:34.616
A little longer if you bring back the gold
from Dragonstone.

96
00:09:34.699 --> 00:09:37.494
But to administer
all of the Seven Kingdoms--

97
00:09:37.577 --> 00:09:40.205
No. What of my coronation?

98
00:09:40.288 --> 00:09:41.873
Oh. you must know something.

99
00:09:41.956 --> 00:09:43.415
They told me little.

100
00:09:43.500 --> 00:09:45.251
Perhaps because they trusted me little.

101
00:09:45.335 --> 00:09:46.920
Do you trust his word. Lord Corlys?

102
00:09:47.003 --> 00:09:49.672
I do not believe he knows
where the gold is.

103
00:09:49.756 --> 00:09:51.800
And I fancy I can sniff a lie.

104
00:09:51.883 --> 00:09:52.884
No one asked you.

105
00:09:54.844 --> 00:09:59.432
It is the duty of
my Mistress of Whisperers to advise me.

106
00:09:59.516 --> 00:10:01.893
After the Gullet.
we must presume Ser Tyland dead.

107
00:10:03.186 --> 00:10:04.687
But he must have told someone.

108
00:10:04.771 --> 00:10:06.689
If he did. it would have been Lord Jasper.

109
00:10:08.191 --> 00:10:09.984
"Ironrod."

110
00:10:11.277 --> 00:10:12.362
Oh. dear.

111
00:10:15.490 --> 00:10:17.742
Our circumstances are...

112
00:10:20.120 --> 00:10:21.412
unfortunate.

113
00:10:21.496 --> 00:10:23.540
But this remains.
I must have a coronation.

114
00:10:24.791 --> 00:10:26.292
Aegon's was done in haste.

115
00:10:27.585 --> 00:10:29.921
Mine must be proper
and leave the realm in no doubt

116
00:10:30.004 --> 00:10:31.714
as to who now rules them.

117
00:10:31.798 --> 00:10:34.926
It seems to me. my queen.

118
00:10:35.009 --> 00:10:38.805
that to go to such expense
while your people still suffer

119
00:10:38.888 --> 00:10:41.224
might set a bitter taste in their mouths.

120
00:10:42.392 --> 00:10:45.103
It is not mere vanity.
It is a matter of legitimacy.

121
00:10:45.186 --> 00:10:46.688
The Triarchy navy is finished.

122
00:10:46.771 --> 00:10:49.315
but the pirates who survived
have come ashore.

123
00:10:49.399 --> 00:10:51.192
They are sacking villages.

124
00:10:51.276 --> 00:10:54.195
They are taking women
and demanding ransoms none can pay.

125
00:10:54.279 --> 00:10:56.698
And difficulties abound in the city.
Your Grace.

126
00:10:56.781 --> 00:10:58.700
It seems the granaries are near empty.

127
00:10:58.783 --> 00:11:02.162
The fields lie fallow
and the planting season is moons away.

128
00:11:02.245 --> 00:11:03.872
If we could find some trade--

129
00:11:03.955 --> 00:11:06.583
It will take time for the routes
to be reestablished.

130
00:11:07.625 --> 00:11:09.210
And we have not enough ships now

131
00:11:09.294 --> 00:11:11.337
to ensure the safety of goods
on the high sea.

132
00:11:11.421 --> 00:11:13.381
Well. in the meantime.
we must find grain for bread

133
00:11:13.464 --> 00:11:14.966
or have the people go hungry again.

134
00:11:15.049 --> 00:11:19.554
It is a never-ending inconvenience.
this insistence of the people being fed.

135
00:11:19.637 --> 00:11:22.098
And yet. a hungry population
is a dangerous one.

136
00:11:22.182 --> 00:11:24.058
as the queen and I well know.

137
00:11:24.142 --> 00:11:27.270
How much time will
we squander here on trifles?

138
00:11:27.353 --> 00:11:28.479
The war is won.

139
00:11:28.563 --> 00:11:30.815
Send another raven to Casterly Rock.

140
00:11:30.899 --> 00:11:35.403
If Tyland secreted gold there.
we will have an answer from Lady Johanna.

141
00:11:35.486 --> 00:11:39.324
Send to all the great houses.
In fact. tell them...

142
00:11:40.325 --> 00:11:42.535
their queen demands tribute.

143
00:11:42.619 --> 00:11:44.704
Remind them who now commands the realm.

144
00:11:44.787 --> 00:11:47.874
Will you not bring your small council here
from Dragonstone?

145
00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:50.501
There is much to take in hand.

146
00:11:50.585 --> 00:11:54.255
They betrayed me in their silence.
if not in deed.

147
00:11:54.339 --> 00:11:55.465
I have done with them.

148
00:11:57.675 --> 00:11:59.344
Where is Aemond?

149
00:11:59.427 --> 00:12:02.055
He burned Daemon's garrison at Harrenhal

150
00:12:02.138 --> 00:12:04.224
and slew the castellan and his sons.

151
00:12:05.558 --> 00:12:07.644
And then. he disappeared.

152
00:12:10.480 --> 00:12:13.274
It is days now since Vhagar was last seen.

153
00:12:14.692 --> 00:12:17.737
There was a woman there.
a maester of sorts.

154
00:12:17.820 --> 00:12:19.489
I have not heard tell of her.

155
00:12:19.572 --> 00:12:21.616
Aemond would not dare challenge you here.

156
00:12:21.699 --> 00:12:24.118
No. But I want him found.

157
00:12:24.202 --> 00:12:25.828
And Sheepstealer as well.

158
00:12:26.913 --> 00:12:29.999
They are the dangers.
Let Baela fly as a scout.

159
00:12:30.083 --> 00:12:33.544
Start at Harrenhal and report
when there are sightings.

160
00:12:33.628 --> 00:12:37.715
I will. in addition. offer a bounty
for the capture of their riders.

161
00:12:37.799 --> 00:12:39.968
We don't have a bounty. it seems.

162
00:12:41.135 --> 00:12:42.387
We will find one.

163
00:12:42.470 --> 00:12:44.055
Ah. better yet.

164
00:12:44.138 --> 00:12:47.517
to the slayer of Aemond One-Eye.
I will grant Harrenhal itself.

165
00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:50.061
I have no need of it now.
All the Riverlands are mine.

166
00:12:52.480 --> 00:12:55.525
Ah. yes. Aegon hanged
all the rat catchers.

167
00:12:58.403 --> 00:13:00.613
As honored as I am
to act as your protector.

168
00:13:00.697 --> 00:13:03.324
my place is with my men in the city.

169
00:13:03.408 --> 00:13:06.286
I would counsel you to appoint
a Queensguard as a matter of urgency.

170
00:13:06.369 --> 00:13:08.162
Daemon will be useful
in identifying candidates.

171
00:13:08.246 --> 00:13:10.665
-We'll put the matter to him.
-My queen. a moment.

172
00:13:10.748 --> 00:13:13.584
It seems rats have eaten through
a large store of candles.

173
00:13:13.668 --> 00:13:15.920
Tallow is short.
we must requisition a new supply

174
00:13:16.004 --> 00:13:17.839
or sit in darkness.

175
00:13:17.922 --> 00:13:20.383
-Then requisition it.
-Of course. There is none yet

176
00:13:20.466 --> 00:13:21.926
-to control the royal purse.
-Begging your pardon. good ser.

177
00:13:22.010 --> 00:13:23.469
In the matter of the bed chamber.

178
00:13:23.553 --> 00:13:25.471
-I didn't know who to ask.
-It's a matter for later.

179
00:13:25.555 --> 00:13:27.432
Hightower bannerman control the Arbor.

180
00:13:27.515 --> 00:13:29.851
-My lady. the price of good wine...
-Move back!

181
00:13:29.934 --> 00:13:31.936
...has tripled. if not more.

182
00:13:32.020 --> 00:13:33.396
Enough. enough!

183
00:13:34.814 --> 00:13:37.900
There is time aplenty in the coming days
to discuss the royal tipple.

184
00:13:38.901 --> 00:13:40.069
Where is my gold?

185
00:13:42.071 --> 00:13:44.991
-Your gold?
-The crown's gold. the treasury.

186
00:13:45.074 --> 00:13:47.660
-Oh. you cannot claim ignorance.
-I'm of no help to you.

187
00:13:47.744 --> 00:13:49.579
It was the Master of Coin who removed it.

188
00:13:49.662 --> 00:13:51.372
And the queen knew nothing of it?

189
00:13:51.456 --> 00:13:53.165
They hated me from the start.

190
00:13:53.249 --> 00:13:55.251
Resented my influence. my mere presence.

191
00:13:55.335 --> 00:13:56.669
My own father kept their plot from me.

192
00:13:56.753 --> 00:13:58.046
Is that so?

193
00:13:58.129 --> 00:14:01.424
I would refer you to the man himself.
but you slew him without ceremony.

194
00:14:02.342 --> 00:14:03.843
Did it make you feel better?

195
00:14:05.428 --> 00:14:06.637
About losing Jace?

196
00:14:10.558 --> 00:14:13.227
I would rather have slain Aegon
as your mother and I had agreed.

197
00:14:14.729 --> 00:14:17.231
But here we are. He is gone.

198
00:14:17.315 --> 00:14:19.275
And I cannot believe
you had no hand in that either.

199
00:14:19.359 --> 00:14:20.860
He did that to himself.

200
00:14:20.943 --> 00:14:22.528
Aegon was fled when
I returned from Dragonstone.

201
00:14:22.612 --> 00:14:24.364
Has Orwyle not given you his account?

202
00:14:24.447 --> 00:14:28.034
His account. or yours?
Do not treat me as a fool.

203
00:14:28.117 --> 00:14:29.577
If you require me to foresee

204
00:14:29.660 --> 00:14:31.704
every duplicitous scheme
devised by Larys Strong.

205
00:14:31.788 --> 00:14:33.539
I confess I cannot help but fall short.

206
00:14:33.623 --> 00:14:34.874
Where is Vhagar?

207
00:14:34.957 --> 00:14:37.585
-Who rides Sheepstealer?
-I do not know!

208
00:14:37.668 --> 00:14:40.505
Is Aemond not flown away as I promised?

209
00:14:40.588 --> 00:14:42.632
Did the guards on the parapets
not suffer you to pass?

210
00:14:42.715 --> 00:14:45.093
I have done all I could.

211
00:14:45.176 --> 00:14:47.470
Will you blame me only
for what men have done?

212
00:14:47.553 --> 00:14:52.058
You promised we could go.
We told the guards. We ran.

213
00:14:56.938 --> 00:14:58.606
No one knows what he looks like.

214
00:14:59.982 --> 00:15:01.609
Aegon.

215
00:15:01.692 --> 00:15:03.569
He's scarred and burned.

216
00:15:03.653 --> 00:15:05.863
His dragon is dead.
Declare him dead as well.

217
00:15:07.323 --> 00:15:09.951
He cannot fight.
and if Larys tries to raise him up...

218
00:15:10.868 --> 00:15:13.704
you can dismiss him as an impostor.

219
00:15:20.128 --> 00:15:21.546
You argue still for his life?

220
00:15:24.799 --> 00:15:26.300
You killed my father.

221
00:15:44.861 --> 00:15:45.862
When...

222
00:15:47.113 --> 00:15:49.782
Aemond has been found...

223
00:15:51.492 --> 00:15:53.995
and the challenge to me...

224
00:15:55.163 --> 00:15:57.832
removed. you will go free.

225
00:15:57.915 --> 00:16:00.793
But until then. I cannot be seen
to favor Hightowers.

226
00:16:01.752 --> 00:16:03.588
I don't want to stay in this room.

227
00:16:03.671 --> 00:16:05.214
I will not treat you unkindly.

228
00:16:06.507 --> 00:16:09.886
You will be fed and clothed and...

229
00:16:11.095 --> 00:16:13.806
and have a maid to suit your needs.

230
00:16:13.890 --> 00:16:15.641
You may walk under guard in the Godswood

231
00:16:15.725 --> 00:16:18.686
and I will have Jaehaera brought to you
for an hour every few days or so.

232
00:16:18.769 --> 00:16:20.688
You cannot mean this. Rhaenyra. please.

233
00:16:20.771 --> 00:16:22.523
None of this pleases me.

234
00:16:25.610 --> 00:16:28.029
So my position is such that I must hope...

235
00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:30.823
for the capture and death of my son.

236
00:16:35.119 --> 00:16:36.704
I can only imagine.

237
00:16:38.164 --> 00:16:40.790
I want it proclaimed that
we discovered Aegon here. dead.

238
00:16:42.210 --> 00:16:44.086
-A shrewd gambit. Your Grace.
-And let Joffrey

239
00:16:44.170 --> 00:16:45.630
be brought back from the Vale.

240
00:16:45.713 --> 00:16:48.049
He is next in line.
He must now be raised as my heir.

241
00:16:53.846 --> 00:16:57.058
I know much about this place.
but never seen it before today.

242
00:16:57.141 --> 00:16:58.643
Is it as you imagined?

243
00:16:58.726 --> 00:17:01.354
It is both larger and smaller.

244
00:17:01.437 --> 00:17:04.315
I will guess that Alicent
had no confidence to give you

245
00:17:04.397 --> 00:17:05.858
as to the whereabouts of the gold.

246
00:17:05.942 --> 00:17:07.108
She did not.

247
00:17:07.193 --> 00:17:08.486
And you trust her yet?

248
00:17:11.906 --> 00:17:13.782
She is a Hightower.

249
00:17:13.866 --> 00:17:15.326
True.

250
00:17:15.409 --> 00:17:17.537
But would I not be simple
to think that in a house

251
00:17:17.619 --> 00:17:19.997
as big as this one.
there were only one rat?

252
00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:24.210
I am much troubled about her son Daeron.

253
00:17:24.292 --> 00:17:26.253
-whom we now hold captive.
-Does she know?

254
00:17:26.337 --> 00:17:29.131
By rights. I should have
his head for a traitor.

255
00:17:29.215 --> 00:17:32.426
He is an heir to Aegon
and a threat to you.

256
00:17:32.510 --> 00:17:34.679
Yet he is also my half-brother
and has not committed the crimes

257
00:17:34.762 --> 00:17:36.681
that Aegon and Aemond have. and yet is...

258
00:17:54.240 --> 00:17:56.784
Why should I not kill him?
Why should I not...

259
00:17:57.702 --> 00:17:59.912
strike him as my own sons were stricken?

260
00:18:00.955 --> 00:18:02.456
There is none to stop you.

261
00:18:03.666 --> 00:18:06.627
There are mountains to be dealt with.
and I have none yet to trust with them.

262
00:18:06.711 --> 00:18:08.838
My lady-in-waiting. Elinda?

263
00:18:08.921 --> 00:18:10.464
Elinda Massey is now in the city.

264
00:18:10.548 --> 00:18:12.967
-having served us well there.
-Better send to her.

265
00:18:13.050 --> 00:18:16.929
And Mysaria. let the staff be questioned.

266
00:18:18.014 --> 00:18:19.557
Quietly. as only you can.

267
00:18:20.725 --> 00:18:23.561
Those who cleave to
the Hightowers must be replaced.

268
00:18:25.855 --> 00:18:27.481
Immediately. Your Grace.

269
00:18:29.025 --> 00:18:30.151
Good morrow. Your Grace.

270
00:18:33.863 --> 00:18:36.032
A blessing in the name
of the Seven Who Are One.

271
00:18:40.745 --> 00:18:43.706
I thank you
for your swift attendance here.

272
00:18:43.789 --> 00:18:45.958
Much has changed in the last few days.

273
00:18:46.042 --> 00:18:48.336
These are turbulent times.

274
00:18:49.670 --> 00:18:53.257
I must for the time being
forego a right and proper coronation.

275
00:18:53.341 --> 00:18:55.718
but I still wish at least to be anointed.

276
00:18:55.801 --> 00:18:58.262
by you. in full sight of the people.

277
00:19:00.473 --> 00:19:02.975
Alas. that it cannot be done.

278
00:19:04.894 --> 00:19:06.437
For what reason?

279
00:19:08.356 --> 00:19:10.983
Some months ago
I anointed your brother Aegon

280
00:19:13.027 --> 00:19:17.406
and declared him the rightful king
before gods and men.

281
00:19:17.490 --> 00:19:20.242
Yes. Aegon is dead.
and I now sit the throne.

282
00:19:25.081 --> 00:19:26.415
So you now say.

283
00:19:27.416 --> 00:19:29.418
Is it your contention that I am a liar?

284
00:19:31.003 --> 00:19:32.713
We have not seen his remains.

285
00:19:35.007 --> 00:19:37.885
Nor have the Silent Sisters
been summoned to tend to them.

286
00:19:40.930 --> 00:19:42.014
You understand

287
00:19:43.140 --> 00:19:46.894
that if there has been some kind of error.

288
00:19:46.977 --> 00:19:48.979
Oh. there has been no error.

289
00:19:49.063 --> 00:19:51.399
I am my father's heir.

290
00:19:51.482 --> 00:19:53.109
And the gods themselves

291
00:19:53.192 --> 00:19:54.902
decree that I must rule
the Seven Kingdoms.

292
00:19:54.985 --> 00:19:57.113
Have they not raised me up

293
00:19:57.196 --> 00:19:59.031
and cast the usurper into ruin?

294
00:19:59.115 --> 00:20:00.574
That has happened. It is true.

295
00:20:00.658 --> 00:20:02.201
How has it happened
if they did not will it?

296
00:20:05.162 --> 00:20:08.499
A dragon appeared to me
in my greatest need.

297
00:20:08.582 --> 00:20:11.335
My gods do not deal in dragons.

298
00:20:12.461 --> 00:20:14.880
They are a profane magic

299
00:20:14.964 --> 00:20:18.217
created in darkness and pride and lust

300
00:20:18.300 --> 00:20:19.927
for power. for impunity.

301
00:20:21.011 --> 00:20:24.557
They destroy. but they do not create.

302
00:20:25.349 --> 00:20:27.351
There is no good that can come of them.

303
00:20:34.191 --> 00:20:36.485
You have made your position
exceedingly clear.

304
00:20:38.696 --> 00:20:42.700
With respect. I advise you.
do not make an enemy of the Faith.

305
00:20:43.951 --> 00:20:47.371
It exhorts and comforts
and binds together your people.

306
00:20:48.664 --> 00:20:50.541
Underestimate it at your peril.

307
00:20:52.793 --> 00:20:56.422
I must confess to you now
a thing you may have guessed before.

308
00:20:58.549 --> 00:21:00.634
Alyn of Hull and his brother Addam
are my sons.

309
00:21:02.011 --> 00:21:06.265
They are born of a woman.
a shipwright I met on my earlier travels.

310
00:21:07.808 --> 00:21:09.477
I did not claim them as mine.

311
00:21:11.145 --> 00:21:12.313
I was ashamed.

312
00:21:13.355 --> 00:21:16.233
And I dreaded grieving Rhaenys. my wife.

313
00:21:16.317 --> 00:21:20.821
And I am grateful
she showed me grace before she died.

314
00:21:23.699 --> 00:21:25.576
I did not guess.

315
00:21:26.911 --> 00:21:31.248
Though I believe I see it now.

316
00:21:33.542 --> 00:21:35.628
You need fear no reproach from me.

317
00:21:35.711 --> 00:21:39.423
It is many a lord who has mixed
noble and common blood.

318
00:21:39.507 --> 00:21:42.802
Their sons are no less stout of heart.

319
00:21:46.096 --> 00:21:49.475
Each has shown himself worthy of more
than was given him before now.

320
00:21:49.558 --> 00:21:52.728
Indeed. we owe Alyn a great debt

321
00:21:52.812 --> 00:21:55.397
for his valiance in both the Stepstones.
and lately in the Gullet.

322
00:21:56.398 --> 00:21:58.818
You have shown yourself a leader of men.

323
00:21:58.901 --> 00:22:01.487
I was only doing my duty. Your Grace.

324
00:22:02.404 --> 00:22:05.366
And Addam has been my assurance
that the gods favor me.

325
00:22:06.492 --> 00:22:08.410
When my hope had waned. they sent me you.

326
00:22:09.286 --> 00:22:11.330
It is my great honor to serve you.
Your Grace.

327
00:22:19.088 --> 00:22:20.881
To that end. my queen...

328
00:22:22.550 --> 00:22:25.177
I have acknowledged my sons.

329
00:22:25.261 --> 00:22:26.887
Mm.

330
00:22:26.971 --> 00:22:30.474
And more than that.
I would name Alyn my heir.

331
00:22:35.521 --> 00:22:38.482
I ask that you legitimize them.

332
00:22:39.775 --> 00:22:41.986
Let them now be Velaryons.

333
00:22:43.362 --> 00:22:44.572
Lords of the realm.

334
00:22:45.948 --> 00:22:48.033
For without them.

335
00:22:48.117 --> 00:22:49.577
my line is ended...

336
00:22:50.744 --> 00:22:52.162
and my name erased.

337
00:22:59.420 --> 00:23:03.424
It is well that you have found an heir.

338
00:23:04.967 --> 00:23:07.261
We have both of us suffered greatly
and I...

339
00:23:08.554 --> 00:23:10.306
I cannot begrudge you a new way forward.

340
00:23:10.389 --> 00:23:12.892
-but Lord Corlys--
-A word from the throne.

341
00:23:14.351 --> 00:23:15.978
It is simple enough.

342
00:25:05.462 --> 00:25:07.172
Are your nerves steady. Your Grace?

343
00:25:07.256 --> 00:25:08.966
As steady as they may be.

344
00:25:10.175 --> 00:25:11.677
I have courted the smallfolk from afar.

345
00:25:11.760 --> 00:25:13.929
but I have not yet come
before them as their queen.

346
00:25:14.013 --> 00:25:15.848
You have been much anticipated.

347
00:25:16.932 --> 00:25:20.561
Then. there will be much expected.

348
00:25:21.562 --> 00:25:22.771
And our resources are few.

349
00:25:22.855 --> 00:25:24.732
I do not know
what satisfaction I can give.

350
00:25:26.817 --> 00:25:30.237
For some. it will be enough to
say they have looked on a queen.

351
00:25:32.614 --> 00:25:34.033
Will I bring your jewels?

352
00:25:36.785 --> 00:25:39.288
I will wear no needless ornament.

353
00:25:39.371 --> 00:25:42.499
I must show strength. readiness.

354
00:25:42.583 --> 00:25:44.126
But the sword perhaps.

355
00:25:44.960 --> 00:25:47.546
Might that not contradict
what you wish to convey

356
00:25:47.629 --> 00:25:49.339
to petitioners in need?

357
00:25:51.050 --> 00:25:52.843
Fair point.

358
00:25:52.926 --> 00:25:53.927
Still.

359
00:25:56.096 --> 00:25:59.016
A chain. I think. For gravity.

360
00:25:59.892 --> 00:26:01.018
One of these.

361
00:26:02.144 --> 00:26:03.145
Fuck.

362
00:26:03.228 --> 00:26:04.229
Your Grace?

363
00:26:05.230 --> 00:26:06.440
I'm bleeding.

364
00:26:07.524 --> 00:26:08.692
-You're sure?
-Yes.

365
00:26:08.776 --> 00:26:10.110
Fuck!

366
00:26:12.237 --> 00:26:13.697
Of course.

367
00:26:13.781 --> 00:26:15.324
I'll fetch some cloths.

368
00:26:16.450 --> 00:26:19.203
Rhaenyra Targaryen. First of Her Name.

369
00:26:19.286 --> 00:26:23.040
Queen of the Andals.
the Rhoynar. and the First Men.

370
00:26:23.123 --> 00:26:26.794
Lady of the Seven Kingdoms.
and Protector of the Realm.

371
00:26:27.920 --> 00:26:32.007
Your Grace. I am a weaver
and my trade is in wool.

372
00:26:32.925 --> 00:26:35.177
We have a great shortage now in fleece.

373
00:26:35.260 --> 00:26:38.597
and such sheep as there are
have been taken by dragons.

374
00:26:41.308 --> 00:26:44.603
Might not the fleece be harvested
before the animal is consumed?

375
00:26:44.686 --> 00:26:46.105
That seems easy enough.

376
00:26:46.188 --> 00:26:51.151
It would be a help. surely.
but there are many in our guild.

377
00:26:51.235 --> 00:26:54.571
To restore our resources.
we would need an investment.

378
00:26:55.572 --> 00:26:57.533
Five hundred golden dragons.

379
00:26:59.326 --> 00:27:01.662
With regards to the sheep. my queen...

380
00:27:02.913 --> 00:27:05.374
such an outcome does nothing
to supply us with meat.

381
00:27:06.333 --> 00:27:09.336
-We butchers have no trade.
-Is there no game to be had?

382
00:27:09.419 --> 00:27:11.255
Oh. not for miles.

383
00:27:11.338 --> 00:27:14.133
And all the hunters
have been taken for archers.

384
00:27:14.216 --> 00:27:16.218
If we could but receive some expenditure

385
00:27:16.301 --> 00:27:18.554
-from the crown--
-Might we consider the Kingswood?

386
00:27:21.056 --> 00:27:23.767
That would be a bold gesture. Your Grace.

387
00:27:23.851 --> 00:27:26.395
One that would have offended
your royal forebears.

388
00:27:27.855 --> 00:27:30.107
Neither stags nor boars.

389
00:27:30.190 --> 00:27:32.609
but rabbits. perhaps.

390
00:27:32.693 --> 00:27:35.863
It bears discussion
in a forum other than this one.

391
00:27:36.780 --> 00:27:38.240
Let the next petitioner come.

392
00:27:39.158 --> 00:27:41.493
I am Sylvi. Your Grace.

393
00:27:41.577 --> 00:27:43.245
I was privileged to be of assistance

394
00:27:43.328 --> 00:27:46.665
to the Lady Mysaria in her campaign
against the usurper.

395
00:27:47.583 --> 00:27:51.003
I thank you. and all here
who kept the faith.

396
00:27:51.086 --> 00:27:53.422
My appeal is not for coin

397
00:27:54.464 --> 00:27:58.886
but for justice for what the commonfolk
have suffered these long months.

398
00:28:01.972 --> 00:28:04.808
The blockade is lifted.
It will not be long now

399
00:28:04.892 --> 00:28:06.768
-before trade routes are reestablished--
-It was not only the blockade

400
00:28:06.852 --> 00:28:09.354
that drove us to want. Your Grace.

401
00:28:11.231 --> 00:28:14.610
It was the rich. The noble lords.

402
00:28:14.693 --> 00:28:17.196
They bought up everything
they could for their storehouses

403
00:28:17.279 --> 00:28:19.031
and left the poorer folk with nothing.

404
00:28:20.199 --> 00:28:21.200
Is this true?

405
00:28:21.283 --> 00:28:24.286
I am no innocent. my queen.

406
00:28:24.369 --> 00:28:26.163
It is the way of the world.

407
00:28:26.246 --> 00:28:28.165
But when the highborn
take even what little remains

408
00:28:28.248 --> 00:28:31.668
and put it aside.
while the lowborn starve...

409
00:28:33.670 --> 00:28:36.298
then that is a matter
I would put before my queen...

410
00:28:37.758 --> 00:28:41.970
who came to power
as a champion of her people.

411
00:28:53.649 --> 00:28:55.901
It is a dangerous element
that seeks to blame the wealthy

412
00:28:55.984 --> 00:28:57.653
for the city's woes.

413
00:28:57.736 --> 00:29:00.322
In a war. all suffer.

414
00:29:00.405 --> 00:29:03.075
-Some more than others.
-That has ever been so.

415
00:29:03.158 --> 00:29:05.369
And yet. in times like these.
it is a cudgel

416
00:29:05.452 --> 00:29:09.289
in irresponsible hands used
to strike up unrest and rebellion.

417
00:29:09.373 --> 00:29:10.874
-Do the commonfolk...
-For the cramps.

418
00:29:10.958 --> 00:29:14.169
...not deserve the providence
and protection of their ruler?

419
00:29:14.253 --> 00:29:16.088
It is a covenant broken

420
00:29:16.171 --> 00:29:18.090
at our peril.

421
00:29:18.173 --> 00:29:19.591
They look to us for order and security.

422
00:29:19.675 --> 00:29:22.928
They look to us for meat
and fuel for their fires.

423
00:29:23.011 --> 00:29:25.138
And who is us. in your telling?

424
00:29:25.222 --> 00:29:30.060
I have earned my seat at this table.
though I was not born to it.

425
00:29:30.143 --> 00:29:33.188
I will leave others to judge
which path most has merit.

426
00:29:33.272 --> 00:29:35.274
Has Baela returned?

427
00:29:35.357 --> 00:29:37.067
What news of Vhagar and Sheepstealer?

428
00:29:37.150 --> 00:29:38.986
The only dragon she saw was Sunfyre.

429
00:29:40.070 --> 00:29:41.446
Long dead and decaying.

430
00:29:41.530 --> 00:29:43.115
She flies again this evening.

431
00:29:43.198 --> 00:29:44.866
Let us send Addam with her.

432
00:29:46.201 --> 00:29:47.703
They cannot hide for long.

433
00:29:50.163 --> 00:29:51.415
You will have justice.

434
00:29:51.498 --> 00:29:53.083
I will never have justice.

435
00:29:54.459 --> 00:29:58.046
But what crumbs of it may be snatched.
I will devour.

436
00:30:00.632 --> 00:30:02.009
In the meantime. Your Grace.

437
00:30:02.092 --> 00:30:03.927
I urge you. turn your mind
to the issue before us--

438
00:30:04.011 --> 00:30:05.429
There is no issue.
There are bellyachers

439
00:30:05.512 --> 00:30:07.931
bleating their dissatisfaction
at the order of things.

440
00:30:08.015 --> 00:30:09.016
Lord Corlys.

441
00:30:11.101 --> 00:30:12.394
I defer to the queen.

442
00:30:13.687 --> 00:30:14.855
Useless.

443
00:30:16.023 --> 00:30:17.858
What would your father do?

444
00:30:24.698 --> 00:30:26.742
A banquet. I think.

445
00:30:34.958 --> 00:30:36.918
Great day for the three of you.

446
00:30:37.002 --> 00:30:39.046
We are much honored. Your Grace.

447
00:30:39.129 --> 00:30:41.840
Ulf. how will you style yourself?

448
00:30:41.923 --> 00:30:43.258
Oh...

449
00:30:44.843 --> 00:30:46.261
Targaryen. Your Grace.

450
00:30:46.345 --> 00:30:47.804
Oh. absolutely not.

451
00:30:50.515 --> 00:30:52.309
Then. I have no style.

452
00:30:52.392 --> 00:30:54.353
So fashion one.

453
00:30:57.731 --> 00:30:58.899
White. then?

454
00:31:02.861 --> 00:31:04.738
Good. and you?

455
00:31:06.907 --> 00:31:09.368
I'm a blacksmith by trade. Your Grace.

456
00:31:10.619 --> 00:31:11.703
I go by Hammer.

457
00:31:14.122 --> 00:31:15.457
Hugh the Hammer.

458
00:31:16.375 --> 00:31:17.834
Ulf the White.

459
00:31:24.007 --> 00:31:25.675
And Addam of Hull.

460
00:31:35.102 --> 00:31:36.228
Kneel.

461
00:31:47.030 --> 00:31:50.617
In the name of the Warrior.
I charge you to be brave.

462
00:31:57.374 --> 00:32:00.419
In the name of the Father.
I charge you to be just.

463
00:32:04.589 --> 00:32:05.841
In the name of the Mother.

464
00:32:05.924 --> 00:32:08.802
I charge you to defend
the young and the innocent.

465
00:32:16.309 --> 00:32:19.229
-Is that it?
-Ser Ulf.

466
00:32:21.565 --> 00:32:24.234
Ser Hugh. Ser Addam.

467
00:32:24.317 --> 00:32:26.611
Knights in your queen's service.

468
00:32:26.695 --> 00:32:29.865
Will you swear fealty to your ruler
and her cause?

469
00:32:29.948 --> 00:32:33.452
To be servants and agents of the crown
for all of your days?

470
00:32:33.535 --> 00:32:35.203
I swear it. Your Grace.

471
00:32:36.538 --> 00:32:38.290
As do I.

472
00:32:38.373 --> 00:32:40.125
Until death.

473
00:32:40.208 --> 00:32:44.337
Ser Luthor. I wish to consult with you
about a notion I have.

474
00:32:44.421 --> 00:32:47.257
A dinner for various nobles
whom you may identify--

475
00:32:47.340 --> 00:32:48.550
Your Grace.

476
00:32:51.511 --> 00:32:55.223
I was wondering what sort
of living I may expect.

477
00:32:55.307 --> 00:32:57.309
now that we're in King's Landing.

478
00:32:58.810 --> 00:33:00.187
Yes. of course.

479
00:33:01.730 --> 00:33:03.648
I did promise to provide
for you and your wife.

480
00:33:03.732 --> 00:33:06.193
She's gone.
I went into the city to find her.

481
00:33:06.276 --> 00:33:08.445
only to hear that she's gone
to live with her brother in Tumbleton.

482
00:33:08.528 --> 00:33:10.322
There was nothing for her here.

483
00:33:10.405 --> 00:33:15.243
Send to her. and we will set aside
a house for you on Visenya's Hill.

484
00:33:15.327 --> 00:33:18.538
And when might that be. Your Grace?

485
00:33:18.622 --> 00:33:20.165
As soon as I am able.

486
00:33:20.248 --> 00:33:23.168
I have no small council at present.

487
00:33:24.544 --> 00:33:26.004
Nor a Queensguard to serve me.

488
00:33:26.087 --> 00:33:29.758
I am awash in dilemmas and deficiencies.

489
00:33:29.841 --> 00:33:33.637
Let me find my footing.
and I will attend to your requests.

490
00:33:41.144 --> 00:33:43.271
The queen dowager. Your Grace.

491
00:33:47.651 --> 00:33:48.652
Very well.

492
00:33:59.120 --> 00:34:00.288
With thanks.

493
00:34:03.083 --> 00:34:04.084
Your Grace.

494
00:34:05.544 --> 00:34:07.546
I'm sorry I was sharp when we spoke.

495
00:34:10.507 --> 00:34:12.592
I have a small request only.

496
00:34:14.427 --> 00:34:16.179
We'll hear it.

497
00:34:17.472 --> 00:34:21.101
Only that my father's remains
be sent to Oldtown...

498
00:34:22.393 --> 00:34:24.187
where they may lie beside my mother's.

499
00:34:33.154 --> 00:34:34.614
As you say.

500
00:34:34.697 --> 00:34:35.907
Thank you.

501
00:34:47.835 --> 00:34:50.714
It is odd to be here with you.

502
00:34:52.757 --> 00:34:53.757
Alicent.

503
00:35:03.101 --> 00:35:06.771
You ruled this realm in all
but name while my father lay ill.

504
00:35:08.523 --> 00:35:09.649
I did.

505
00:35:14.571 --> 00:35:15.697
I heard...

506
00:35:16.698 --> 00:35:18.199
petitions today.

507
00:35:21.786 --> 00:35:23.413
There are many of them.

508
00:35:24.748 --> 00:35:26.625
And their needs are many more. It's a...

509
00:35:27.792 --> 00:35:29.753
heavy weight.

510
00:35:33.673 --> 00:35:35.258
How did you bear it?

511
00:35:38.595 --> 00:35:39.638
In truth?

512
00:35:44.809 --> 00:35:48.855
You may not rule and remain yourself.

513
00:35:52.359 --> 00:35:56.613
There are choices to be made
and you may. on occasion.

514
00:35:56.696 --> 00:35:59.449
have to turn your face away
while people suffer and die.

515
00:36:01.951 --> 00:36:03.787
There is in you a door that must shut.

516
00:36:05.246 --> 00:36:09.959
You will do things
that your heart would have recoiled from

517
00:36:10.043 --> 00:36:11.419
before you came to the throne.

518
00:36:12.879 --> 00:36:14.631
I acknowledge the struggle.

519
00:36:15.674 --> 00:36:17.467
But I dispute that
I must become what I am not.

520
00:36:20.637 --> 00:36:21.930
Time will tell.

521
00:36:24.349 --> 00:36:25.934
My father remained himself.

522
00:36:26.017 --> 00:36:28.895
Your father lived in
a world of his own construction.

523
00:36:28.978 --> 00:36:30.980
You and I have never set foot there.

524
00:36:35.402 --> 00:36:36.695
Be welcome.

525
00:36:39.781 --> 00:36:42.158
You have all heard. I'm sure.

526
00:36:42.242 --> 00:36:45.286
that our ascension is proclaimed
throughout the realm.

527
00:36:45.370 --> 00:36:47.831
Already the Hightowers
have bent the knee before me.

528
00:36:47.914 --> 00:36:52.043
and. likewise. those in this room
have pledged their loyalty.

529
00:36:54.212 --> 00:36:56.214
Later than I would have liked.

530
00:36:56.297 --> 00:36:59.718
But I come before you as a conciliator.

531
00:37:11.521 --> 00:37:14.566
It is our privilege. Your Grace.

532
00:37:14.649 --> 00:37:17.277
to attend you here at last.

533
00:37:18.278 --> 00:37:21.573
I avow. which all here know.

534
00:37:21.656 --> 00:37:24.993
that I mistrusted the Hightower claim
from the beginning.

535
00:37:26.494 --> 00:37:27.996
I'm sure that's true.

536
00:37:28.079 --> 00:37:30.915
even if I heard no tale of you
rising up to protest it.

537
00:37:32.792 --> 00:37:35.628
Ah. I see our feast is served.

538
00:38:03.531 --> 00:38:04.741
What is this?

539
00:38:06.701 --> 00:38:09.412
This is what the commonfolk
of my city ate.

540
00:38:09.496 --> 00:38:12.373
this and worse.
while you and those like you

541
00:38:12.457 --> 00:38:14.209
hid provisions away in your storehouses.

542
00:38:15.627 --> 00:38:17.879
Your Grace. we were afraid.

543
00:38:17.962 --> 00:38:20.590
Will you have had us starve
and our families with us?

544
00:38:20.673 --> 00:38:21.925
I would have no one starve.

545
00:38:22.008 --> 00:38:24.093
I would have those with much

546
00:38:24.177 --> 00:38:27.597
exercise stewardship
and tend to those with little.

547
00:38:27.680 --> 00:38:29.766
as a shepherd tends to their sheep.

548
00:38:29.849 --> 00:38:32.477
The poor. like rats. overrun the city.

549
00:38:32.560 --> 00:38:34.896
They thieve and fight for every crumb.

550
00:38:34.979 --> 00:38:37.816
And would you not do the same
if your children were hungry?

551
00:38:37.899 --> 00:38:39.317
No. I would not.

552
00:38:39.400 --> 00:38:40.777
Admirable restraint.

553
00:38:40.860 --> 00:38:43.321
You would lie genteel in your grave.

554
00:38:45.031 --> 00:38:49.244
As you sit here. my Gold Cloaks
are entering each of your houses.

555
00:38:49.327 --> 00:38:53.832
They are searching your storerooms
for all that you hoarded away.

556
00:38:53.915 --> 00:38:55.500
And they will bring
what they find back to me

557
00:38:55.583 --> 00:38:58.419
for distribution to those
in my city who need it.

558
00:38:58.503 --> 00:39:01.130
-This is unconscionable.
-We're being robbed!

559
00:39:01.214 --> 00:39:05.218
What the crown demands of you
is not plunder. but a duty.

560
00:39:05.301 --> 00:39:07.095
And tonight. will serve as a lesson

561
00:39:07.178 --> 00:39:10.348
in what I will require of you
now and henceforth.

562
00:39:10.431 --> 00:39:11.516
Good evening.

563
00:39:24.070 --> 00:39:25.321
Your Grace.

564
00:39:29.659 --> 00:39:31.369
House Manderly. is it?

565
00:39:31.452 --> 00:39:34.873
Ser Torrhen Manderly. Your Grace.
your humble servant.

566
00:39:35.915 --> 00:39:38.751
Is it humility that causes you
to smile so. Ser Torrhen?

567
00:39:39.752 --> 00:39:41.713
It is admiration
only for a hand well played.

568
00:39:42.964 --> 00:39:45.508
My Gold Cloaks will be visitors
to your household as well.

569
00:39:45.592 --> 00:39:48.261
And no doubt I am
as deserving as any here.

570
00:39:49.095 --> 00:39:51.806
It is a bold move.
and the smallfolk will cheer it.

571
00:39:51.890 --> 00:39:54.183
It may even make them forget
that it was your blockade

572
00:39:54.267 --> 00:39:56.185
that made bread scarce in the first place.

573
00:39:59.480 --> 00:40:01.232
Well. rest assured. Ser Torrhen...

574
00:40:02.358 --> 00:40:03.735
my memory is long.

575
00:40:06.237 --> 00:40:08.114
They'll resent you for this.

576
00:40:08.197 --> 00:40:11.242
They are merchants and minor nobles.

577
00:40:11.326 --> 00:40:12.785
They've been in error and they know it.

578
00:40:12.869 --> 00:40:14.287
I do admit. I find it amusing.

579
00:40:14.370 --> 00:40:17.498
It will help a certain number of people
for a certain number of weeks

580
00:40:17.582 --> 00:40:19.042
and do nothing for the rest of them.

581
00:40:19.125 --> 00:40:21.711
-It is a gesture only.
-Yes. and gestures matter.

582
00:40:21.794 --> 00:40:26.257
But you say rightly that
this is not a lasting solution.

583
00:40:26.341 --> 00:40:27.884
For that. I will need you to fly.

584
00:40:29.010 --> 00:40:30.470
Go to the Vale.

585
00:40:30.553 --> 00:40:32.931
Lady Jeyne never sent
the swords she promised.

586
00:40:33.014 --> 00:40:34.557
She may pay her debt in coin.

587
00:40:36.142 --> 00:40:37.810
This is an errand I will relish.

588
00:40:38.853 --> 00:40:41.314
The other great houses I will summon here.

589
00:40:41.397 --> 00:40:42.899
In the meantime. return with gold

590
00:40:42.982 --> 00:40:45.693
or pledges of gold.
else we are hobbled before we begin.

591
00:40:50.865 --> 00:40:53.201
You have come so far.

592
00:40:53.284 --> 00:40:55.453
and yet you still don't know who you are.

593
00:40:56.537 --> 00:41:00.249
If I fail to administer my city.
how will I be trusted to govern a realm?

594
00:41:00.333 --> 00:41:02.001
Aegon the Conqueror had three dragons.

595
00:41:02.085 --> 00:41:05.129
You now have six.
It is a power beyond imagining.

596
00:41:05.213 --> 00:41:07.715
Why scrabble here for gold
when the world lies before us?

597
00:41:07.799 --> 00:41:09.759
Dorne could be ours.

598
00:41:10.802 --> 00:41:14.013
And then Essos and the Free Cities.

599
00:41:14.097 --> 00:41:15.682
Yi Ti and its riches.

600
00:41:19.686 --> 00:41:21.854
They say there is a city
at the edge of the world

601
00:41:21.938 --> 00:41:23.439
where men have wings.

602
00:41:26.943 --> 00:41:29.862
I remember wishing to go there
to see them for myself.

603
00:41:29.946 --> 00:41:32.323
Those men will serve us.
They will serve you.

604
00:41:35.326 --> 00:41:37.620
You will have an empire unassailable.

605
00:41:39.330 --> 00:41:41.582
And our children will rule it
forever and a day.

606
00:41:41.666 --> 00:41:45.294
You style us commandeers and marauders
like the pirates that plague us.

607
00:41:45.378 --> 00:41:47.171
I style us gods. Rhaenyra.

608
00:41:51.384 --> 00:41:53.177
As we were always meant to be.

609
00:42:26.461 --> 00:42:28.004
And I've made my peace with him.

610
00:42:29.338 --> 00:42:30.923
But he renounced his dragon.

611
00:42:55.948 --> 00:42:57.200
Your Grace.

612
00:43:01.120 --> 00:43:02.663
You still have to kill Daeron.

613
00:43:54.632 --> 00:43:56.259
You are tired today.

614
00:43:57.385 --> 00:43:58.886
I cannot sleep in that bed.

615
00:43:58.970 --> 00:44:01.347
Mm. a new mattress. perhaps.

616
00:44:03.599 --> 00:44:04.642
Perhaps.

617
00:44:07.019 --> 00:44:09.272
You have buried your grief.

618
00:44:09.355 --> 00:44:11.440
I feel no grief. I feel nothing.

619
00:44:14.569 --> 00:44:17.280
Well. no. There is rage.

620
00:44:20.241 --> 00:44:22.243
A rage that billows beyond my grasp.

621
00:44:23.161 --> 00:44:24.453
I have known such rage.

622
00:44:30.626 --> 00:44:33.171
I will look on those
who killed my sons. Mysaria.

623
00:44:35.173 --> 00:44:36.174
I will.

624
00:44:54.692 --> 00:44:57.236
Let the Septon deny you.

625
00:44:57.320 --> 00:44:58.905
This will be your anointing.

626
00:45:08.581 --> 00:45:11.083
Rhaenyra! Rhaenyra!

627
00:45:14.253 --> 00:45:17.423
I have been away too long.

628
00:45:18.799 --> 00:45:22.929
But we are at last reunited.

629
00:45:31.520 --> 00:45:33.564
The usurpers are vanquished.

630
00:45:33.648 --> 00:45:35.691
and I have taken my rightful throne...

631
00:45:37.276 --> 00:45:40.780
from which I shall rule judiciously...

632
00:45:41.781 --> 00:45:45.243
with strength. but also mercy...

633
00:45:46.327 --> 00:45:49.080
as befits a true queen.

634
00:45:53.709 --> 00:45:57.505
In token of which I bring you gifts
for your relief.

635
00:46:01.300 --> 00:46:05.721
And in honor of my father
who came before me.

636
00:46:08.724 --> 00:46:10.101
Gods be with you.

637
00:46:37.962 --> 00:46:38.963
Your Grace.

638
00:46:41.048 --> 00:46:43.050
-A word.
-Walk with me.

639
00:46:44.010 --> 00:46:45.511
You made Addam a knight.

640
00:46:45.594 --> 00:46:49.015
but it seems you styled him Hull
rather than Velaryon.

641
00:46:49.098 --> 00:46:50.808
We had agreed. I thought.

642
00:46:50.891 --> 00:46:53.352
that he and Alyn would be legitimized.

643
00:46:53.436 --> 00:46:55.730
Now. if it is a matter of ceremony or...

644
00:46:58.190 --> 00:47:02.403
I'm sorry. Corlys.
but in this moment I cannot do as you ask.

645
00:47:05.364 --> 00:47:11.203
I have given all I had.
everything. in service to you.

646
00:47:12.413 --> 00:47:14.123
My castle lies in ashes.

647
00:47:14.206 --> 00:47:16.625
and I have asked no favor
in return but this.

648
00:47:18.377 --> 00:47:22.381
You know very well the rumors
that have dogged my sons from the first.

649
00:47:23.674 --> 00:47:25.801
My reign has just begun.

650
00:47:25.885 --> 00:47:29.347
I cannot in this moment
be seen to raise up those...

651
00:47:31.182 --> 00:47:33.225
born outside of noble troth. I...

652
00:47:35.144 --> 00:47:37.104
And so you will insult my house...

653
00:47:38.481 --> 00:47:40.983
so that you may be seen
to be something you are not.

654
00:47:42.151 --> 00:47:43.694
I have Joffrey to think of.

655
00:47:43.778 --> 00:47:47.615
I was staunch in my defense
when your own troth was...

656
00:47:47.698 --> 00:47:48.741
doubted.

657
00:47:48.824 --> 00:47:52.745
Yes. and I thank you for this.
among many other things.

658
00:47:53.746 --> 00:47:55.706
But all eyes look to me now.

659
00:47:56.957 --> 00:48:00.628
Perhaps one day when there
is not so much scrutiny--

660
00:48:00.711 --> 00:48:02.213
You are ashamed.

661
00:48:04.131 --> 00:48:05.674
Well...

662
00:48:05.758 --> 00:48:08.511
-It is a matter of legitimacy.
-Your son Joffrey...

663
00:48:09.887 --> 00:48:11.180
is a bastard.

664
00:48:13.224 --> 00:48:14.850
Your son. Lucerys.

665
00:48:14.934 --> 00:48:17.353
whom I accepted as my heir...

666
00:48:18.896 --> 00:48:20.689
-was a bastard.
-Lord Corlys.

667
00:48:20.773 --> 00:48:24.443
Your son Jacaerys
lived and died a bastard!

668
00:48:28.030 --> 00:48:32.326
Say aloud to me the reason your children
deserve what mine are denied.

669
00:48:39.083 --> 00:48:41.836
Helaena has gone
to the Godswood. with thanks.

670
00:48:41.919 --> 00:48:45.923
I have your son Daeron here
within these walls.

671
00:48:49.135 --> 00:48:50.761
Here since when?

672
00:48:50.845 --> 00:48:52.721
He was delivered to me two days ago

673
00:48:52.805 --> 00:48:57.309
as part of the terms under which
your cousin surrendered.

674
00:49:05.317 --> 00:49:06.569
And what do you...

675
00:49:07.570 --> 00:49:08.988
what do you plan to do with him?

676
00:49:09.905 --> 00:49:11.740
By rights. I should have his head. but...

677
00:49:12.825 --> 00:49:15.411
he had no part in his brothers' treachery.

678
00:49:16.704 --> 00:49:19.623
He did only what was
expected of him by his elders.

679
00:49:19.707 --> 00:49:23.878
Therefore. I will send him
north to the Wall.

680
00:49:27.465 --> 00:49:29.800
He will take the Black
and he will not return.

681
00:49:29.884 --> 00:49:31.302
but he will keep his life.

682
00:49:34.889 --> 00:49:36.182
Do you wish me to thank you?

683
00:49:37.766 --> 00:49:39.727
I see you have been merciful.

684
00:49:41.562 --> 00:49:43.647
And yet I grieve for what could have been.

685
00:49:46.817 --> 00:49:49.195
He was sent to ward as an infant.

686
00:49:49.278 --> 00:49:50.905
I've seen him once in the last five years.

687
00:49:50.988 --> 00:49:52.740
I hardly know the boy.

688
00:49:52.823 --> 00:49:54.074
And yet...

689
00:49:56.952 --> 00:50:00.080
From all accounts.
he has borne his lot very bravely.

690
00:50:04.293 --> 00:50:05.711
I wish to see him.

691
00:50:07.129 --> 00:50:11.550
You will join the Night's Watch
and serve out your days there.

692
00:50:13.135 --> 00:50:15.095
It's a hard road.
but there is honor in it.

693
00:50:25.439 --> 00:50:27.733
I see that nothing moves you.
It's a pity.

694
00:50:27.816 --> 00:50:28.984
Your mother is here.

695
00:50:30.778 --> 00:50:33.948
I would counsel you to unguard yourself.

696
00:50:34.823 --> 00:50:37.159
One time at least.
before you take your long journey.

697
00:50:37.243 --> 00:50:38.369
The queen dowager. ser.

698
00:50:46.544 --> 00:50:49.004
Here she is. Look at her.

699
00:51:13.571 --> 00:51:15.030
You don't know this boy.

700
00:51:17.825 --> 00:51:19.285
He is not Daeron.

701
00:51:31.630 --> 00:51:33.632
Who are you then?

702
00:51:33.716 --> 00:51:35.134
Speak!

703
00:51:35.217 --> 00:51:37.052
He compelled me.

704
00:51:37.136 --> 00:51:39.138
-I begged him.
-Who compelled you?

705
00:51:39.221 --> 00:51:40.681
Lord Ormund Hightower.

706
00:51:43.017 --> 00:51:44.810
He blenched my hair.

707
00:51:44.893 --> 00:51:47.021
told me I must play
the part of the prince.

708
00:51:47.938 --> 00:51:49.773
Even if she burned me with dragons.

709
00:51:51.650 --> 00:51:55.529
I must stay silent.
or he would have my mother hanged.

710
00:51:56.905 --> 00:51:58.198
My real mother.

711
00:52:00.409 --> 00:52:02.870
She isn't a queen. Your Grace.

712
00:52:02.953 --> 00:52:06.874
She's only a lady.
and our people are merchants.

713
00:52:06.957 --> 00:52:08.167
Ormund...

714
00:52:09.209 --> 00:52:10.419
has deceived me.

715
00:52:12.588 --> 00:52:14.548
Your real son.
he keeps with him. no doubt.

716
00:52:16.175 --> 00:52:18.427
Did he think I would not discover it?

717
00:52:41.533 --> 00:52:43.118
What game does he play?

718
00:52:46.580 --> 00:52:47.665
Your Grace.

719
00:52:48.499 --> 00:52:50.751
I'm sent to tell you our work here
is all but complete.

720
00:52:50.834 --> 00:52:53.212
The Hightower colors have been
removed throughout these walls.

721
00:52:54.505 --> 00:52:55.881
Burn all of it.

722
00:52:59.718 --> 00:53:00.761
Your Grace.

723
00:53:00.844 --> 00:53:02.429
There's a dragonkeeper at the gate.

724
00:53:07.142 --> 00:53:08.310
What is it?

725
00:53:20.572 --> 00:53:22.074
-What?
-Yeah.
